22/08/2003
VIDIN, Bulgaria -- Geological studies on the construction of a second bridge over the Danube River connecting Bulgaria and Romania start on Friday (22 August), according to the transport and communications ministry. 
The studies will continue for three months, with actual construction scheduled to begin in May 2004. 
The total cost could reach 300m euros. 
(Dnevnik, Trud - 22/08/03; BTA -21/08/03)
